=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Overviews_Operators_ex30 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 264 Hz, featuring punchy attack and dynamic envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: dynamic
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 263.9016
  harmonic_decay_rate: -2.4758
  harmonic_regularity: 0.0297
  pitch_clarity: 63.4143
  inharmonicity: 0.2313
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -12.5963
  resonance_freq: 796.7285

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Operators Example 30
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Overviews/Operators.html
// Tags: Operators, Overviews
// ---
// --- Example 30 ---
(
{
    var a, b;
    a = FSinOsc.ar(800);
    b = FSinOsc.ar(XLine.kr(200,500,5));
    ((a * b) + a + b) * 0.125
}.play)
